This paper proposes a method for deep batch active learning, which involves both querying and training processes. The paper focuses on the theoretical insights and principles behind the proposed method, which are based on distribution matching using Wasserstein distance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
